This paper discusses the interpretability of rule-based models in machine learning and data mining, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on the plausibility of models, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) as users need to understand and trust the models. Additionally, the paper mentions cognitive biases, which is a topic in social and information sciences (cs.SI).
